# File Structure

```
app/<route>/                    Next.js App Router pages
  page.tsx                      Route entry point
  loading.tsx                   Skeleton (optional)

src/common/                     Shared across all features
  components/                   Layout, navbar, shared wrappers
  hooks/                        Custom React hooks
  lib/                          DB clients (supabase/), utilities
  providers/                    Context providers (theme, query)
  repository/                   Base repository classes and types
  services/                     Base service classes
  styles/                       Global CSS, design tokens
  types/                        Domain type definitions
  ui/                           shadcn/ui primitives

src/features/<feature>/         One folder per feature
  components/                   React components (kebab-case.tsx)
  styles/                       PascalCase .styles.ts (1:1 with components)
  services/                     Business logic layer
  repository/                   Data access interfaces + implementations
```

## Naming Rules

- Components: `kebab-case.tsx` (e.g., `task-summary.tsx`)
- Style files: `PascalCase.styles.ts` (e.g., `TaskSummary.styles.ts`)
- Services: `camelCase` + `Service` suffix (e.g., `taskService.ts`)
- Repository interfaces: `camelCaseRepository.ts`
- Repository implementations: `supabaseXRepository.ts` or `firebaseXRepository.ts`
- Types: defined in `src/common/types/index.ts`, exported as named interfaces

## Style Convention

Use TypeScript style objects (`export const styles = { ... } as const`), not CSS Modules. Each key maps to a Tailwind class string. Never use `.module.css` files.
